text:
Hi team,
We have two users in the dev canton wallet associated with the same party hint (both users are able to see the coin balance). We want to offboard one user. We tried the using the offboard API, /v0/admin/users/offboard . This worked and we were able to offboard the user. But when the same user onboards again, they are able to see the same party ID and the coin balance as well. Is this expected? What can we do to make sure only one user has access?

The second solution we tried was <https://github.com/global-synchronizer-foundation/docs/discussions/26>. We faced an issue with finding the user ID in the second step. Giving the <oauth-user-id> did not work. Got this error in the output -
```DecodedCantonError(
  code = 'USER_NOT_FOUND',
  category = InvalidGivenCurrentSystemStateResourceMissing,
  cause = "getting user failed for unknown user "auth0|<ID>"",
  traceId = '<traceId>',
  context = Seq('participant=>'participant'', 'definite_answer=>false'),
  resources = 'USER=>auth0|<ID>'
)```
Can anyone clarify what value we could have given here? Thanks.
